Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteNetWeight(25.10)                                  deleteNetWeight(25.10)

Name
       deleteNetWeight - Removes the net weight values on the specified nets

Syntax
        deleteNetWeight

       [-help]

       {-all | <netName> ...}

       Removes  the  net weight values on the specified nets. You can use this
       command after running the specifyNetWeightcommand.

Parameters
       -all   Specifies the removal of net weight values on all nets.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each deleteNetWeight parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all

              of its parameters, use the man command:

              man deleteNetWeight

       <netName>
              Specifies the net names, separated by spaces, for which the  net
              weight values are removed.

              Data_type: string, required

Related Information
              * specifyNetWeight

              * getNetWeight

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

